# Swift Tooling and Build System

Swift Package Manager, Xcode, static analysis, and CI pipelines.

## Swift Package Manager

```swift
// swift-tools-version: 6.0
let package = Package(
    name: "MyApp",
    platforms: [.iOS(.v17), .macOS(.v14)],
    products: [
        .library(name: "MyAppCore", targets: ["MyAppCore"]),
    ],
    dependencies: [
        .package(url: "https://github.com/apple/swift-argument-parser", from: "1.3.0"),
        .package(url: "https://github.com/apple/swift-log", from: "1.5.0"),
    ],
    targets: [
        .target(name: "MyAppCore", dependencies: [
            .product(name: "Logging", package: "swift-log"),
        ]),
        .testTarget(name: "MyAppCoreTests", dependencies: ["MyAppCore"]),
    ]
)
```

## Essential Commands

```bash
swift build                          # Debug build
swift build -c release               # Release build
swift test --parallel                # Run tests
swift package resolve                # Resolve deps
swiftlint --strict                   # Static analysis
```

## Build Settings

