GCC_TREAT_WARNINGS_AS_ERRORS = YES     # Zero-warning policy
SWIFT_TREAT_WARNINGS_AS_ERRORS = YES
```

## Logging

```swift
import os

private let logger = Logger(subsystem: "com.example.myapp", category: "networking")
logger.info("Fetching user \(userId, privacy: .public)")
logger.error("Failed: \(error.localizedDescription, privacy: .public)")
// debug/info not persisted by default — minimal performance cost
```

## CI Essentials

```bash
swift build
swift test --parallel
swiftlint --strict
xcodebuild test -scheme MyApp -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 16'
```

## Anti-Patterns

```swift
// Never: print() for production logging — use os.Logger
// Never: Cocoapods for new projects when SPM works
// Never: Hardcoded strings for UI — use String(localized:)
```
